{'response': 'And when, in the city in which I love you,
Steps echo with yesterday’s longing—
beneath wards outside coffee shops,
a blue light diffuses longing from rain-beaten neon.
Ghosts steer my hand to doorbells—halos swelling swaywise.
There: train-whistles curl through sunspapers, slicing morning air.
Your laughter anchors this raucous mosaic dense with wishes overflowed.
